<TEXT>
the five fendi sisters have tried to save 
their skins just as animal rights activists threatened to make 
them extinct 
the fendi claim to fame as the most innovative elegant furriers 
on the market was about to put them at the head of the 
conservationists wanted list 
they are still using fur but in coats shown wednesday night it 
was used as lining instead of as an outright fashion statement 
the styles too were less elaborate with many downcoats 
parkas and shearlings 
karl lagerfeld the creative genius behind the fendi label 
indulged in what he termed organized confusion dying leather 
in bright shades working it into chamois as soft as silk or 
stuffing it with silk for a down effect 
he also worked over sheepskin detailing it with velvet strands 
folk braiding or panels of tuscan tapestry 
meanwhile inside the coat lurked plush mink or sable out of 
view of animal rights activists who have mounted a campaign to stop 
the use of animal skins in garments 
the opening of a fendi megastore on new yorks fashionable 
fifth avenue this past fall risked being a flop when protesters 
walked out front shouting antifur slogans 
the campaign could hurt the multimilliondollar fendi fashion 
empire which is famous for its furs but even more renowned for 
its leather goods 
but at the end of wednesdays show presented in an elegant 
renaissance palace in downtown milan there was much praise for the 
move from showy furs to discretion 
in the past decade fendi designed by lagerfeld has also become 
one of the top labels of italian readytowear 
the new fallwinter 199091 collection presented during the fur 
show was short and sexy with lots of demure coat dresses cute wool 
skating skirts and ribbed wool miniskirts often worn over thick 
wool tights and leg warmers 
to go under the sportier jackets fendi presented skintight 
stretch jeans with bright velvet braiding often coupled with 
thighhigh supersoft suede boots 
</TEXT>
