the new federal agricultural mortgage corp 
called farmer mac for short is tuning up for its grand entry in 
the financial market later this year 
farmer mac was created a little more than two years ago by the 
agricultural credit act of 1987 as a secondary market for 
agricultural real estate loans 
but it has taken time to organize to work out the kinks and 
follow the instructions congress laid down farmer mac officials 
said wednesday 
startup procedures included the initial sale of 20 million in 
voting common stock to banks and other lenders rules and operating 
specifications are still being honed 
john r dahl chairman of the board said after the 
corporations second annual stockholders meeting that underwriting 
standards and other guides must be developed meticulously to ensure 
integrity 
