dianne feinstein has catapulted from 
last to first in the governors race partly because of a tv 
commercial that shows her announcing the assassination of her 
predecessor as san francisco mayor 
feinsteins surge in the campaign to succeed retiring republican 
gov george deukmejian has turned a quiet contest between two 
cautious men into a lively and unpredictable race 
during most of the past year the 56yearold feinstein was the 
forgotten third candidate in a race dominated by republican us 
sen pete wilson and state attorney general john van de kamp a 
democrat 
feinstein had suffered several setbacks early in the race 
her recuperation from a hysterectomy canceled two months of 
public appearances her first campaign manager clint reilly quit 
and complained that she was unwilling to commit to a schedule an 
organization and a budget prompting jokes that he was the first 
campaign manager to fire the candidate and her fundraising lagged 
millions of dollars behind that of her rivals 
polls reported her up to 18 points behind van de kamp whom she 
faces in the june 5 democratic primary and 11 points behind wilson 
in a general election matchup political columnists speculated 
about when she would drop out 
but in a doordie effort feinstein and her husband richard 
blum put up their own money for a 600000 blitz of tv commercials 
in late january and early february mostly in los angeles where she 
was not well known 
feinsteins 30second commercial opens with blackandwhite 1978 
footage of feinstein then president of the san francisco board of 
supervisors announcing at a news conference that mayor george 
moscone and supervisor harvey milk had just been shot 
stressing that she showed tough and caring leadership in a 
time of tragedy the commercial also cited feinsteins prochoice 
stand on abortion and described her as the only democrat for 
governor for the death penalty all three candidates are 
prochoice wilson supports the death penalty van de kamp opposes 
it 
six polls by three independent pollsters tracked a dramatic 
shift from october van de kamps large lead became a large 
deficit one late february poll put feinstein ahead 43 percent to 
24 percent the poll also had her in front of wilson 44 percent to 
33 percent 
steve teichner who conducted three of those six polls said 
that an unusually large 29 percent of the voters he surveyed could 
describe the feinstein commercials without prompting and that 
voters recalling the ad had a favorable impression of feinstein by 
4to1 
teichner cautioned however that the large shift based on one 
commercial is a sign that voters are fickle 
it also means a large number of voters out there are seeking a 
personality candidate teichner said he noted that feinsteins 
standing as the first woman to seriously compete for governor of 
california created a more exciting image than that of her two 
rivals 
the race is open and its volatile and nobody is questioning 
any more that dianne has a viable candidacy said feinstein 
spokeswoman dee dee myers 
feinsteins sudden emergence as frontrunner has dramatically 
changed the tenor of the race 
van de kamp 54 shifted tactics abruptly in late february with 
scathing attacks on feinsteins fiscal environmental and civil 
rights record during her nine years as mayor 
wilson 56 also has joined in attacking feinstein for leaving 
a budget deficit for her democratic successor in san francisco art 
agnos 
its now abundantly clear that were going to have a 
democratic primary that were going to have a real race van de 
kamp said 
