sandinistas are trying to make confiscations legal 
but theyre also leaving an empty shell of a state structure 
that will make it harder for uno to function as a government 
in the northcentral town of matagalpa uno legal adviser 
santiago rivas said the sandinistas are gutting state enterprises 
he said government officials are giving state property away 
emptying sugar and coffee warehouses registering state vehicles in 
private names or selling them off 
although he offered no proof rivas said officials also are 
funneling public money into foreign bank accounts 
we are going to take over a government totally in ruins 
rivas said we are inheriting a bankrupt government 
a bill allowing tenants to claim legal ownership of state 
housing was to be read before the sandinistadominated national 
assembly today 
the bill covers more than 10000 homes nationwide the homes 
have been awarded rented or loaned to the tenants usually 
sandinista party militants or government officials many of the 
previous owners were supporters associates or relatives of 
dictator anastasio somoza who the sandinistas overthrew 
some homes were seized by the state through the law of 
absence under which nicaraguans who leave the country for more 
than six months are subject to the confiscation of their property 
the law was aimed at antisandinista exiles who fled nicaragua 
by the thousands after the july 1979 sandinista revolution 
but in other cases people who just happened to be living 
outside the country for longer than six months returned to find 
their homes occupied by sandinista officials 
in principle the reigning idea is to award the houses to the 
people already living in them as long as they belong to the 
state said rafael solis first secretary and deputy of the 
national assembly 
but well have to see what solution we give to those persons 
occupying privately owned homes 
the singlechamber national assembly now is dominated by the 
sandinistas who have 61 seats to 35 from six opposition parties 
come april 25 however uno will be dominant with election 
returns showing it gained 52 seats to 39 for the sandinistas an 
extremeleft party the revolutionary unity movement obtained one 
seat 
uno leaders have said they do not plan to simply return all 
confiscated property but to establish special tribunals that will 
