<TEXT>
joseph melvin lyle a vice admiral in the 
navy supply corps who was director of the defense supply agency 
before retiring in 1967 has died at the age of 77 
lyle who held some of the highest logistics posts in the armed 
services died of cancer tuesday at a nursing home 
a resident of reston lyle was born in augusta ga he graduated 
from the us naval academy at annapolis in 1935 
he was an assistant supply officer at pearl harbor hawaii when 
the japanese attacked it on dec 7 1941 he remained in pearl 
harbor until 1944 then spent the next two years as supply officer 
at the norfolk naval air station in virginia 
in subsequent years he served in various capacities in hawaii 
and philadelphia california and washington he graduated from the 
naval war college in newport ri 
in 1961 lyle became deputy director of the newly formed defense 
supply agency now called the defense logistics agency in 1964 he 
was named director and held that post until retiring from the 
service 
after leaving the navy lyle joined the national security 
industrial association he retired as president in 1977 
survivors include a son dr jerry manning lyle of rockville 
md and two grandchildren 
