florida atlantic university this fall 
will become the states only public university offering free 
tuition to every black freshman who meets admissions standards 
school officials said 
the gesture which the united negro college fund said was 
probably the only such program in the nation is intended to boost 
the number of black students at the school in boca raton 
sometimes you spend too much time talking about why you should 
do something and not enough time doing it fau president anthony 
catanese said tuesday if youre serious about recruiting the 
best students a full scholarship simply is the way to go 
there also is a practical motive the board of regents has 
ordered fau to increase its freshman class by 50 percent next year 
and the number of black students must go up to meet state targets 
for minority enrollment 
its a phenomenal idea an excellent first step said 
maurice hall president of the west palm beach branch of the naacp 
both floridians and outofstate students can apply but 
instate students will get preference under the program which will 
be financed through private donations and school funds 
fau has 608 black students including foreign students out of 
a total student body of 11310 
but this years freshman class had only 28 black students that 
meets the board of regents target for blacks who must account for 
at least 77 percent of the student body but it is smaller than 
the proportion of blacks in surrounding broward and palm beach 
counties 112 percent and 135 percent 
the targets are far too low for this area said brian 
levinstankevich admissions director it should be obvious to 
anybody that 28 black freshmen students are not enough 
what bothers me is that the goals are rather modest i want to 
redouble the efforts catanese said 
university officials emphasized that boosting the number of 
blacks will not require cutting the number of nonblack students 
because freshman enrollment is being expanded so dramatically 
were not displacing anybody by adding minorities 
levinstankevich said i think thats an important point 
enough scholarship money already is earmarked to pay full 
tuition costs for 30 black freshmen every black freshman this year 
has a scholarship financial aid officials estimate that tuition 
will be 1350 a student next year 
fau would be the only university in the nation to guarantee full 
scholarships to each black freshman the united negro college fund 
