the general trend presented in milan this 
week during the italian fallwinter 199091 readytowear 
collection is ultrashort and sporty 
but two designers never known to follow the fashion pack 
gianfranco ferre and giorgio armani went their own way showing 
discreet hemlines and more town than country clothes 
ferre who also designs for dior in paris presents a woman used 
to living in the lap of luxury the gold theme is threaded 
throughout his collection appearing from the early hours of the 
morning in gray mohair sweaters painted with gold to be worn over 
flannel sweat pants 
this theme becomes ever more opulent as the day goes on with 
rich gold embroidery on silk brocade jackets and coats for the 
cocktail hour and shimmery gold evening gowns for the grande 
soiree 
the ferre skirt stops a discreet inch above the knee and the 
elegant hemline is enhanced by the simplicity of the footwear 
suede or silk moderately heeled pumps 
the overall look is closer to couture than ready to wear and 
definitely separates itself from the myriad of fastfashion mini 
skirts knit body suits ski jackets and thigh boots that have 
permeated the milan runway this week 
ferre did indulge in a series of gold leather parkas with fur 
trim which looked a bit much on the runway but are sure to be a 
