<TEXT>
lhasa residents passed the first anniversary of 
martial law thursday under heavy security and there were no 
reports of renewed protests by tibetan nationalists 
authorities felt confident enough of their control to allow 
tibets strongly nationalist buddhist monks to hold a major prayer 
