antichinese protests in the past 
the 10day festival which began last week draws hundreds of 
monks to lhasas ancient jokhang temple last year chinese 
authorities canceled the festival for fear of unrest but tibetans 
held a small march anyway 
police opened fire triggering three days of violent clashes 
that ended when martial law took effect march 8 it was the fourth 
bloody confrontation with tibetan nationalists since 1987 
lhasa authorities who have tightly restricted tourism to the 
remote city in the past year made sure even fewer foreigners would 
be there this week 
