federal centers for disease control said lead exposure is 
devastating to the developing brains and nervous systems of 
fetuses and young children 
experts have steadily reduced their estimate of blood lead 
levels that have toxic effects so that blood lead levels that 
cause concern for young children today 10 to 15 micrograms per 
deciliter are onesixth the levels of concern in the 1960s and 
before houk said 
today in the united states millions of children from all 
geographic areas and socioeconomic strata have blood lead levels 
