asked if the government was planning talks with the militants 
he said you can have talks in an atmosphere of peace 
the militants have in the past rejected negotiations with the 
government saying they wont compromise 
the campaign for an independent kashmir simmering since 1948 
has flared up in recent months with the consolidation of militant 
groups 
