five american writers have been nominated for 
the penfaulkner award for the best works of fiction published in 
1989 the folger shakespeare library announced thursday 
the nominees are russell banks for his novel affliction 
el doctorow for his novel billy bathgate molly gloss for 
her novel the jumpoff creek josephine jacobsen for her 
collection of stories titled on the island and lynne sharon 
schwartz for her novel leaving brooklyn 
the winner of the 1990 award will be announced in april the 
five nominees whose works were chosen from among 250 novels and 
short story collections by a jury of three writers will be honored 
at a ceremony at the folger on may 12 
the penfaulkner award which is administered by the folger was 
founded in 1980 to pay tribute to the late william faulkner who 
used funds from his nobel prize for literature to support other 
writers 
