divergence between the kremlin and cuba as gorbachev moves to 
reduce the power of the communist party in the soviet union 
in the article the weekly moscow news said castro has used 
intransigence and relied on outdated ideas to keep his country in 
check 
it noted that staterun cuban radio carried editorial attacks on 
the collapse of communist regimes in eastern europe and blamed the 
changes on weak governments unable to tackle economic turmoil 
such categorical judgments are pronounced in an island with 
total rationing which insures people against poverty but does not 
give them the impetus to work moscow news said 
it mocked the cuban leader for his dec 7 statement saying if 
history will attach to us the role of the last defenders of 
socialism in the world we will defend this stronghold to the last 
drop of blood 
the cuban model that castro wants to defend is based on a 
complete rejection of a market economy moral principles over 
material ones a militarized state and an untouchable partystate 
elite the newspaper said 
cuba copied none other but soviet administrative and economic 
structures at the time when european socialism was sinking into the 
swamp of stagnation based on the ideological dogma of the late 
leader leonid i brezhnev it said 
cuba gets about 5 billion in annual aid from the soviet union 
despite castros pledge to defend the party at all costs and 
ignore change in the socialist community moscow news said about 15 
dissident groups have emerged in cuba 
state department spokeswoman margaret tutwiler said thursday it 
is not surprising that a soviet newspaper should be critical of 
cuba 
cuba remains a rigid police state she said at a time 
where the soviet government is changing its domestic and foreign 
policies cuba is becoming ever more isolated and rigid 
obviously cuba is out of step and resisting the rising tide 
of change she said castro is isolated even among socialist 
countries 
