further denies that it leaked any information relating to the 
inquiry 
the fbi is acutely aware of its obligations to protect the 
rights of employees who use legal procedures available to them to 
express their grievances the directors statement continued 
allegations of retaliation against any employee for having taken 
advantage of these procedures are taken very seriously by the fbi 
and if confirmed will be met with stern disciplinary action 
allegations that information of an official nature may have been 
leaked by any fbi employee for any reason will likewise be met with 
stern disciplinary action if confirmed 
mata who in 1983 received the justice departments top award 
for counterespionage has said that in 1988 shortly before his 
testimony in the discrimination case he was confronted with 
allegations that he compromised national security while working 
undercover no charges have ever been filed against him 
the case against mr mata is a house of cards said silva 
an el paso texas attorney who represented mata in the bias case 
heard by us district judge lucius d bunton in el paso there 
is no substance whatsoever to the allegations silva said it 
is nothing more than reprisals and retaliation against him 
bunton ruled that the fbi had demonstrated a pattern of 
discrimination against hispanics called its affirmative action 
program bankrupt and ordered sweeping changes in its promotion 
policies a special panel headed by former rep barbara jordan 
dtexas is about to begin its evaluation of the fbis compliance 
and mata and others are expected to testify once more 
in miami rodriguez matas other attorney said it is very 
ironic that those hearings are going to go forth next month and 
that allegations against mr mata and other agents are all of a 
sudden surfacing he said minor administrative actions had been 
taken against about 10 others involved in the lawsuit including 
agents in el paso and san antonio texas los angeles san juan 
puerto rico and atlanta 
overall there are 425 hispanic agents among the fbis 10000 
employees according to rodriguez himself a former agent 
