valley icing roads and breaking tree limbs and power lines in 
parts of nebraska south dakota iowa minnesota and wisconsin 
at midday freezing rain occasionally mixed with snow 
continued to fall from northeastern minnesota across central 
minnesota and central wisconsin 
the freezing rain across minnesota was expected to change to 
snow during the night accumulating to 1 to 3 inches by friday 
morning 
snow was scattered over the nebraska panhandle 
rain fell across western and southern wisconsin and the 
remainder of the southern twothirds of minnesota 
rain and occasional thunderstorms also reached across northern 
iowa illinois indiana western south carolina western north 
carolina northern georgia northern alabama southern tennessee 
