<TEXT>
the dade county school board late wednesday 
selected paul w bell a 30year veteran of the school system as 
the new superintendent of the district containing miami 
bell deputy superintendent for education for dade county 
schools since 1987 succeeds joseph a fernandez who left his 
155000ayear post to become chancellor of new york city public 
schools 
the dade county system is the largest school district in florida 
with 282000 students and 264 schools and the fourth largest in 
the nation after new york los angeles and chicago 
the board voted 43 to approve bell for the job on the 17th 
ballot then chose to make the decision unanimous said dade county 
schools spokesman andy gollan 
the board unable to reach a majority decision on a new 
superintendent after 16 ballots deferred the issue and took care 
of other business until several hours later in the meeting gollan 
said 
a contract for bell 56 whose salary is subject to negotiation 
is expected to be submitted at the boards next meeting on march 
21 gollan said 
other contenders for the post included dade county associate 
superintendents james fleming and solomon stinson san diego 
superintendent thomas payzant and indianapolis superintendent james 
adams 
the board initially waffled on whether to conduct a nationwide 
search or choose someone locally after fernandez was picked for his 
new job in september but the panel spent the last four months 
conducting a national search at a cost of 60000 
tee s greer jr who did not actively pursue the 
superintendency served as acting superintendent after fernandez 
assumed his new position on jan 1 gollan said 
bell joined the dade county system in 1960 as a teacher he has 
a masters degree in education from the university of louisville in 
kentucky where he also received his bachelors degree 
</TEXT>
