chase untermeyer says that being george bushs 
chief talent scout is rather like painting the golden gate 
bridge 
once you finish the job you have to start in at the other end 
and start painting it again says the 44yearold white house 
personnel director and bush protege 
from a crowded office in the west wing of the white house 
untermeyer and his staff assemble resumes and sort out the winners 
from the alsorans in the quest for presidential appointments 
with white house chief of staff john sununu the affable 
houstonraised and harvardtrained untermeyer makes the final 
recommendations to bush on 3500 jobs untermayer and his staff 
also ride herd on cabinet and agency heads in filling more than 
2000 other political posts 
untermeyer once a political reporter said in a recent 
interview that its sort of a rule of thumb in this business 
that every time you make an appointment you earn nine enemies and 
one ingrate 
there also has been some criticism of the speed with which the 
white house has filled appointments last september democrats on 
capitol hill accused bush of operating a swisscheese 
govermnent riddled with highlevel vacancies 
untermeyer defends the administrations performance saying that 
background checks are timeconsuming and that the criticism would 
have been far worse if we had slamdunked people into jobs 
i personally dont mind being the target of a bad news story 
or two in 1989 if we are spared in 1990 and thereafter a series of 
news stories about some cretin or boob or otherwise incompetent 
individual who was named to office by george bush he told the 
heritage foundation last year 
you can bet that the folks writing those stories would not 
say on the other hand the white house in 1989 acted with 
admirable speed in putting this fine citizen into office said 
untermeyer 
in the interview untermeyer said the opposition turned up the 
heat on the pace of appointments essentially because we had 
denied the democrats the socalled sleaze issue 
practically none of our nominees has come under any 
controversy whereas that happened all the time under president 
reagan 
however several bush nominees to major posts were defeated or 
