<TEXT>
here is a chronology of major events in the life 
of president mikhail s gorbachev 
march 2 1931 mikhail sergeyevich gorbachev is born in 
privolnoye a town in the stavropol region of southern russia 
1950 enters moscow state university to study law 
1952 becomes a full member of the communist party and active 
its youth organization komsomol 
1954 marries fellow student raisa maximovna titorenko 
1955 returns to stavropol and begins fulltime work for 
komsomol 
1960 becomes first secretary of stavropol regional komsomol 
1966 named to lead the party organization in stavropol 
1969 elevated to full membership in national communist party 
central committee 
1971 chosen as deputy of the supreme soviet 
1978 becomes the central committee secretary in charge of 
agriculture and moves to moscow 
1979 made a candidate or nonvoting member of the ruling 
politburo led by president leonid i brezhnev 
1980 elevated to full membership in politburo 
march 11 1985 becomes general secretary of the communist 
party after death of konstantin u chernenko 
november 1985 holds first summit in geneva with president 
ronald reagan four full summits follow over the next five years 
1986 begins his reform program in earnest with the catchwords 
glasnost meaning openness and selfcriticism and 
perestroika the russian word for restructuring releases 
andrei d sakharov from internal exile 
1987 he and reagan sign a treaty to eliminate both sides 
mediumrange nuclear weapons 
1988 calls the first communist party conference since the days 
of josef stalin to press for greater reform dissolves the supreme 
soviet to be replaced by the congress of peoples deputies and a 
smaller fulltime legislature the new supreme soviet 
1989 withdraws soviet troops from afghanistan and presides 
over congress of peoples deputies that elects him president 
1990 ends communist party monopoly on political power and 
moves to create a stronger presidency 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

