<DOCNO> AP900308-0227 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here is a review of mikhail s gorbachevs record 
since becoming soviet leader on march 11 1985 
foreign policy 
declared policy of nonintervention in eastern europe 
permitting a wave of revolutions that deposed oldstyle communist 
regimes broke down the berlin wall and set the stage for german 
reunification 
dramatically reduced fears of a nuclear war or soviet attacks 
on western europe or china 
cut the defense budget and declared a unilateral reduction in 
forces of 500000 soldiers and 10000 tanks 
informally agreed with united states on troop reductions in 
central europe 
agreed with the united states to destroy mediumrange missiles 
and try for a second treaty in 1990 reducing longrange nuclear 
weapons by 50 percent 
brought home the 115000 soviet soldiers in afghanistan 
changed foreign policy from a struggle with capitalist 
countries to cooperation with them in fulfilling such universal 
human values as the desire for peace and a better life 
democratization 
introduced competitive elections in 1989 won agreement from 
the communist party leadership to end its constitutional monopoly 
on power and vested legislative authority in a new parliament 
proposed broad new presidential powers including the right to 
suspend the legislatures of republics 
promised legal guarantees of a freer press freedom of 
assembly freedom of religion and the right to a fair trial 
released hundreds of political prisoners and ended persecution 
for political views 
virtually opened the borders but has not produced a promised 
law on free exit and entry 
economic policy 
failed to improve the daily life of ordinary soviets who face 
inflation rationing and worse shortages than before delayed 
needed reform of prices that have have no relation to costs and 
waste scarce resources 
won communist party leaderships acceptance of private 
ownership of factories 
obtained parliamentary approval of leasing land to 
individuals with the right of inheritance but refused to legalize 
private ownership of land 
made foreign investment easier through joint ventures 
legalized small private business cooperatives but did not 
guarantee them adequate legal sources of supplies 
revealed the longsecret soviet budget deficit which this 
year reached 90 billion rubles 150 billion at the official rate 
of exchange 
domestic policy 
permitted independence movements to develop in the baltics and 
the caucasus 
sent tens of thousands of soviet soldiers on peacekeeping 
duties in restive republics but could not halt ethnic and 
nationalist conflicts in which 500 people died in the past two 
years 
adopted the cause of environmentalists but succeeded in doing 
little to improve polluted air water and land 
promised a dramatic increase in housing but has achieved no 
visible results 
restricted production of alcoholic beverages to reduce 
alcoholism at a cost to the treasury of billions of rubles 
campaign succeeded in toughening public attitude toward drunkenness 
</TEXT>
