must obtain a waiver under a 1985 federal law such waivers exempt 
the agencies from the federal requirement that medicaid offer the 
same services to all patients 
a study by the rand corp a private nonprofit think tank 
concluded that most state medicaid agencies fail to take advantage 
of the federal law because of complicated application and 
administrative requirements for getting waivers from the health 
care financing administration 
