<TEXT>
robots resembling giraffes and elephant 
trunks snake around halfassembled hondas spewing sparks as they 
weld steel frames and produce a car in 14 hours 
only in japan no an identical factory is churning out hondas 
in ohio thousands of usbuilt hondas will be shipped to japan 
and thousands more of the japanbuilt hondas will be sold in the 
united states 
global is the theme in japans thriving auto industry 
honda toyota and nissan are building more cars abroad and slowly 
blurring the national origin of automobiles historically one of 
the most powerful symbols of a countrys manufacturing might 
the strategy makes sense to japanese auto companies because it 
can deflect or defuse trade tensions from countries growing hostile 
to japans barrage of exports the strategy also places 
manufacturing and assembly closer to buyers which can cut costs 
ultimately much of the profit still flows back to japan 
we do business according to our philosophy of manufacturing 
products in the market in which they are sold says honda senior 
managing director shoichiro irimajiri localization of research and 
production facilities means they can become new supply bases for 
hondas global sales channels 
honda says it is ready to export usmade hondas to europe for 
the first time 
in laborshort japan no one grumbles about exporting jobs to 
fill labor needs the auto industry must hire parttimers who can 
make more than 2700 a month irimajiri said during a tour of 
hondas 9monthold futuristic factory at suzuka in central japan 
conveyers glide silently raising or lowering cars automatically 
depending on the work to be done workers wear slogans on their 
white jumpsuits reading aim for zero accidents 
late last year a sister factory built from the same blueprints 
began producing in ohio one of the latest additions to the 
socalled transplant shops beginning to dot americas 
industrial heartland 
honda was the first japanese automaker to build cars in the 
united states a huge success last year americans bought more 
honda accords than any other car 60 percent of them usmade and 
late last year honda cars were outselling chrysler in the united 
states 
overall japanese car production capacity is likely to top 1 
million in the united states this year and in europe by 1998 
its an increasingly stark contrast to the problems besetting 
american automakers which have been laying off thousands of 
employees and closing factories for weeks at a time because they 
cant sell enough cars 
toyota foresees a 32 percent surge in overseas production this 
year to 650000 cars and mitsubishi motors which operates a 
jointventure plant with chrysler forecasts overseas production up 
33 percent to 410000 hondas production abroad will be up 17 
percent to 525000 nissans up 7 percent to 683000 and mazdas 
steady at 220000 
honda and toyota are following nissans lead in building 
factories in britain mazda is close to announcing a factory built 
jointly with ford probably in west germany chrysler is looking 
for an overseas partner to build a subcompact probably with 
mitsubishi motors 
earlier this month mitsubishis parent company announced it was 
negotiating a cooperation agreement with west germanys 
daimlerbenz group in what could provide the japanese conglomerate 
with an enormous advantage in setting up shop in europe 
none of the japanese have any kind of sales network in 
continental europe and its very expensive to set one up from 
scratch says rama krishna an auto analyst for the investment 
firm first boston asia youll see tieups between japanese and 
local or american manufacturers a lot more joint production 
designing and marketing 
many cars already have hybrid nationality nissans new nxcoupe 
was designed by americans at nissans design subsidiary in 
california and mazdas new navajo sport utility vehicle was 
designed and built by ford mazda builds ford lasers telstars and 
festivas in japan and toyotas joint venture with general motors 
in california makes toyota corollas and geo prizms 
a new twist is shipping foreignmade japanese cars back to 
japan hnda started importing americanmade accords in 1988 and 
toyota plans to start in 1992 mazdabuilt fords have been imported 
since 1988 and nissan may do the same from its plant in britain 
honda plans to import 50000 usmade hondas annually by 1991 
quintupling this years imports to japan 
its a totally realistic goal says honda spokesman bret 
anderson now we have the capacity to do it its also economical 
for us and not being done just because of trade frictions 
although japanese car exports to the united states are limited 
to 23 million a year they were still worth 209 billion in 1989 
exports ministry of international trade and industry figures show 
that represents about 40 percent of the us trade deficit with 
japan and has arouseed american protectionist passions and 
warnings 
we the great believers are having our pants pulled down an 
inch at a time by a centrally orchestrated totally committed 
economic aggressor chrysler motors chairman bennett bidwell said 
in a january speech we had better develop a healthy fear of 
economic subordination because we are faced with it 
in europe protectionism is rising as well with carmakers 
pressing for tighter quotas on japanese imports some europeans 
have even proposed that japanese cars built in europe should be 
counted as imports europeans spent a record 10 billion on 
japanese cars last year the japan automobile manufacturers 
association says 
japanese moves into north america and europe have contributed to 
a decline in car exports for the last four years but that trend 
partly disguises the earnings of japanese automakers from their 
foreign operations moreover the value of exports are expected to 
start rising again because of japans expensive new luxury models 
such as toyotas lexus and nissans infiniti 
toyota sold more than 16000 lexuses in the united states in the 
last four months of 1989 nissan got a slower start with sales of 
1700 infinitis but hasnt been selling them as long 
the rising value clearly worries some japanese auto executives 
because it could incite more trade backlashes nissan president 
yutaka kume said his company is attempting to counter the trend by 
importing more auto parts from abroad in what he called an 
internationalization program 
government trade officials also sensitive to hostile foreign 
reaction have asked automakers to keep investment in new plants 
and equipment from resulting in increased shipments overseas 
heightened exports could especially provoke a hostile response 
in the united states where the big three general motors corp 
ford motor co and chrysler corp all reported severe earnings 
declines last year 
by contrast toyotas earnings in the fiscal year ending in july 
were up 17 percent to 21 billion nissan reported a 77 percent 
earnings rise to 868 million in the fiscal year ended last march 
