<TEXT>
elders ixl ltd on thursday announced a major 
restructuring under which it will spin off its agribusiness 
operations into a new public company and sell other assets while 
retaining its brewing business 
elders also said it would buy grand metropolitan plcs breweries 
for an undisclosed amount and enter into a joint venture with grand 
met to operate the two companies 8500 pubs elders had been 
frustrated in past attempts to expand its extensive brewing 
interests 
the announcement was made in sydney australia and a copy was 
made available in london 
the restructuring was intended maximize value for all elders 
shareholders by creating independent corporate entities focused on 
single businesses elders said 
elders chairman john d elliott said the reconstruction will 
position these companies to continue their growth strongly into the 
1990s 
elders ixl will become fosters brewing group ltd and focus on 
its brewing interests the announcement said its bestknown brands 
are fosters and courage 
elders said it would spin off its agribusiness operations by 
creating a new publicly held company called elders ltd and giving 
elders existing shareholders stock in the new company the spinoff 
requires shareholder approval elders said 
other assets including elders ixls interests in elders finance 
group and elders resources nzfp will be sold and the surplus cash 
will be distributed to shareholders over time it said 
harlin holdings pty ltd an australian company that owns 55 
percent of elders stock and supports the restructuring said it 
plans to reduce its interest in fosters brewing to below 50 percent 
and maintain its stake between 40 percent and 50 percent 
harlin will scale down its holding in the agribusiness company 
as well elders said without providing specifics and will retain 
representatives on the two boards of directors 
elders said it has reached an understanding with grand met 
the british food liquor and leisure group that owns pillsbury co 
of the united states to acquire grand mets four breweries 
the 5050 venture to operate pubs will be called inntrepreneur 
estates ltd and will operate elders more than 5000 pubs and 
grand mets more than 2000 pubs 
elders said it intends to make a definitive announcement on the 
brewery purchase and pub joint venture shortly it did not say how 
much it would pay for grand mets brewing interests but it said 
the purchase and the combination of the pubs would offset each 
other the two transactions would be cash neutral it said 
the deal with grand met requires approval from british 
regulatory authorities and of grand mets shareholders elders said 
last year the government blocked elders hostile bid of 16 
billion pounds or 26 billion for the british brewer scottish 
and newcastle plc for competitive reasons 
britains brewers have been seeking to restructure their 
operations since the government in an effort to encourage 
competition decided that brewers could own only 2000 tied 
pubs which sell the owners beers any pubs owned above that number 
have to be free houses selling whatever beer they like 
explaining the restructuring elders said its board of directors 
decided that elders market value does not reflect the value of its 
brewing operations and that the way to rectify that was to create a 
separate brewing company which was likely to be more attractive to 
shareholders 
the restructuring has been a longstanding objective it said 
fosters brewing will have strong competitive positions in 
australia canada and britain and significant potential for future 
growth elders said 
before the grand met deal fosters brewing would be the 
fourthlargest brewing company in the world the company said 
among other things the agribusiness company will be a leading 
provider of farm services in australaia the largest wool broker 
largest livestock sales and rural merchandise supply organization 
and a major provider of financial services to the rural industry 
</TEXT>
