<TEXT>
two small biotechnology companies that have 
devised an aids vaccine have seen their stock shoot higher 
following an official goahead for human testing of the substance 
stock in alpha 1 biomedicals inc of washington dc and 
celsci corp of alexandria va jumped after california health 
officials approved the first phase of human testing 
the approval announced monday was the first for human trials 
of the hgp30 vaccine in the united states according to the 
companies 
those involved in the tests cautioned it could take years for 
the development of a true vaccine 
nevertheless the price of celsci nearly doubled tuesday to 
