viral technologies inc which devised the vaccine the vaccine is 
synthetic it contains no live or dead aids virus components 
unlike many other aids vaccines under study meaning there is no 
chance it could induce infection with the deadly disease 
geert kersten vice president and treasurer of celsci said the 
price of his companys stock has been volatile since it went public 
in 1983 
its a very emotional stock he said 
kersten owns about 15 percent of the 32 million outstanding 
shares while celscis founder maximillian de clara of 
switzerland owns about 9 percent kersten said much of the 
remaining stock is believed to be held by individual investors he 
said 
managers and directors of alpha 1 which went public in 1986 
own about 15 percent of that companys 46 million shares said 
robert j lanham chief operating officer the rest is believed to 
be held by small investors he said 
both companies have lost money since their founding which is 
typical for biotechnology startups 
kersten said viral technologies began testing the vaccine on 
humans in great britain last may so far the results have been 
encouraging with the immune systems of those in the study 
producing the expected defensive response to the aids virus he 
said 
the vaccine targets a core protein of the aids virus which is 
found in all strains of the virus most other potential vaccines 
under study target the outer shell of the virus which can vary 
because the virus often is mutated kersten said 
several other companies also are testing an aids vaccine on 
humans including bristolmyers squibb co a joint venture of 
chiron corp and cibageigy and a joint venture of merck amp co and 
repligen corp said stuart weisbrod an analyst at 
prudentialbache securities inc 
